If you want change, you must be willing to put in the work. But first you have to decide what "fit" looks like to you. Then ask yourself how it would make you feel to be that fit. Finally, make sure it is sustainable. If you have to work to maintain your fitness, then maybe it's time to find a different approach. Having been 117lbs AND also 153lbs. I can tell you 117 was not fun. So let's stop being superficial and more realistic. Find your "fit". Find yourself. 
.
.
📹Angel Aulet

Warm-up weight (35lb): Once upon a time (believe it or not), I couldn't even imagine that I could chest press 35lbs each arm. Today at 41yrs young? 50lbs each arm is my working weight. My point is, building strength is not an overnight achievement. It takes months and even years of focus, training and discipline. And NO it will NOT make you look like a man. But in the same way that building physical strength requires an extraordinary amount of focus, so does building mental strength. So does building your career. So does discovering who you really are. So be patient. Keep your head up and continue to push forward.  Let's get started with building strength. But also, don't forget to FINISH THE JOB! Because we don't stop AT the finish line. We stop only AFTER we've crossed the finish line!
.
#strongbodystrongmind #strength #strong #fitness #athlete #coach

Last Friday was insane due to the weather. Valentina and I took an Uber to school, which cost an arm and 2 legs. But it was the best Uber ride. Believe it or not, all of the other Uber's were $60+ but we ended up getting an Uber Black for way less. The driver proceeded to walk out of the car to open the door for us during the down pour. I declined. But once we were inside, Valentina and I had the best ride. We started by reviewing words for this years Spelling Bee. Then veered off into researching various types of common phobias. We then discovered that there is an aversion/phobia of repetitive patterns and clusters of small holes like honeycombs (Trypophobia)  and finally learned what the longest word in the English Dictionary is (it's 45 letters and couldn't fit the screen). And no it's not supercalafra.... We still got completely soaked but laughed about it. We missed being late by 2 minutes. Overall, it was a fun morning.
My point? You can make the best out of the worst situation. 
Happy Monday!
.
#mondaymotivation #motivation #strength #mindset #fun #mood #monday

Week 6 of my leg program
Front Squats: *4 sets/15 reps
Split stance KB deadlifts: 3 sets/15 reps
Bulgarian split squat: 3 sets/15 reps
.
Not pictured: Hip thrusts and leg press
.
*I was stuck at 10-12 reps for the longest. I literally started hitting that point of failure at rep 10.  But this week I refused to accept it. So I talked to myself "what's 3 more reps?" While 3 more reps may sound easy, it took all my effort but I did it. I pushed past my threshold. Holy shit did it feel good! Now I  maintain for a few more weeks then increase weight. The mind is a beautiful thing. It will take you anywhere you choose if you allow it. It will also hold you back should you accept to be held back.
.
I'm dead today. So cardio it is.
.
🎥 @jjohnnyt_
